THOUGHT: The assertion in computeBestVF assumes a scalar VF plan is always present. In this reproducer, there’s no scalar plan, causing the assert and crash. I will replace the assert with a fallback: if no scalar plan exists, choose the minimal legal VF if available and return its cost; otherwise, disable vectorization. This avoids aborting while keeping reasonable behavior.

```bash
nl -ba llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp | sed -n '7458,7472p' && sed -i '7465,7466c\  if (!hasPlanWithVF(ScalarVF)) {
    ElementCount MinVF = getMinimalLegalVectorizationFactor();
    if (hasPlanWithVF(MinVF)) {
      InstructionCost MinCost = CM.expectedCost(MinVF);
      LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "LV: No scalar plan. Using minimal VF " << MinVF << " with cost " << MinCost << ".\n");
      return VectorizationFactor(MinVF, MinCost, MinCost);
    }
    return VectorizationFactor::Disabled();
  }' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp && submit-patch
```

